  "prompt": "Does blind person from birth dream?",
  "response": "Yes, individuals who are blind from birth do experience dreams, although their dreams may differ from those of sighted individuals. Blind people tend to dream using their other senses, such as sound, touch, taste, and smell. Their dreams often involve experiences, emotions, and interactions that are based on their sensory perceptions and personal experiences rather than visual imagery. \n\nResearch has shown that dreams can be rich in complexity and may involve scenarios and sensations that are vivid and meaningful to the dreamer, even without visual components.",
